@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam rectangleBorderColor #666666
skinparam noteBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam arrowColor #333333

title OpenClaw — Defense-in-Depth Security Architecture\n(threat model: agent container is always considered potentially compromised)

' ══════════════════════════════════════════
'  AGENT HOST
' ══════════════════════════════════════════
rectangle "**Agent Host**" as AgentHost #F0F4FF {

  rectangle "  Host iptables FORWARD chain  \n  <i>scripts/firewall/setup_firewall.sh</i>  " as ForwardFW #FFE0B2

  rectangle "**Docker Agent Container**  [agent-dev · 172.28.0.10]" as AgentCtr #DDEEFF {

    rectangle "  Seccomp blocklist  \n  <i>security/seccomp-agent.json</i>\n  + cap_drop: ALL + selective cap_add  " as Seccomp #FFCCCC

    rectangle "  Internal egress firewall  \n  <i>agents/init-firewall.sh</i>  " as InternalFW #FFCCCC

    rectangle "  ssh-agent  \n  key loaded in tmpfs · source file chmod 000  " as SSHAgent #CCFFCC

    rectangle "  **Agent Process**\n  openclaw | claude --auto-approve | hermes  " as AgentProc #DDEEFF
  }
}

note right of ForwardFW
  SSH egress from container
  locked to IPs listed in
  config.json only.
  All other outbound TCP blocked.
end note

note right of Seccomp
  Blocks: mount, unshare, ptrace,
  bpf, kexec, perf_event_open …
  NET_ADMIN/NET_RAW granted only
  during entrypoint (firewall init),
  then cleared via gosu exec.
end note

note right of InternalFW
  Allowlist: api.anthropic.com,
  npm registry, GitHub, Sentry,
  Statsig, Docker DNS resolver.
  Default: DROP outbound.
end note

note right of SSHAgent
  Agent can authenticate outbound
  SSH sessions but cannot read
  or exfiltrate the private key.
end note

' ══════════════════════════════════════════
'  TARGET HOST
' ══════════════════════════════════════════
rectangle "**Target Host**" as TargetHost #F0FFF0 {

  rectangle "  sshd  \n  PermitOpen · ForceCommand  " as SSHD #FFE0B2

  rectangle "**Workspace Container**  [rootless Docker · AGENT_USER namespace]" as WorkspaceCtr #DDEEFF {

    rectangle "  dev-bot shell session  " as Shell #CCFFDD
  }

  rectangle "  UID-keyed egress filter  \n  <i>scripts/workspace/egress_filter.sh</i>  \n  <i>(egress_filter: true)</i>  " as EgressFilter #FFCCCC

  rectangle "  Docker socket proxy  \n  <i>scripts/workspace/docker_proxy.py</i>  \n  <i>(docker_access: true)</i>  " as DockerProxy #CCFFCC
}

note right of SSHD
  PermitOpen: only forward_ports
  list — sshd rejects all other
  port-forward requests.
  ForceCommand: session_entry.sh
  routes every session into the
  workspace container via
  docker exec — no host shell.
end note

note right of WorkspaceCtr
  ssh, scp, nc, socat, telnet
  stripped from image.
  project_paths bind-mounted RW.
  Agent never touches real
  host filesystem.
end note

note right of EgressFilter
  iptables rules matched by UID.
  Outbound restricted to DNS +
  HTTPS to npm/PyPI/GitHub/
  Docker Hub only.
  Covers rootless Docker egress
  (appears as same UID on host).
end note

note right of DockerProxy
  Intercepts /containers/create.
  Blocks: mounts outside
  project_paths, --privileged,
  network=host, dangerous caps.
  Proxy socket: 0o666 so rootless
  container UID mapping can reach it.
end note

' ══════════════════════════════════════════
'  FLOWS
' ══════════════════════════════════════════
AgentProc       -down->  SSHAgent    : uses
SSHAgent        -right-> ForwardFW   : SSH (ed25519)
ForwardFW       -right-> SSHD        : TCP 22\n(allowed IPs only)
SSHD            -down->  Shell       : docker exec\n(ForceCommand)
Shell           -down->  EgressFilter : all outbound traffic\n(optional layer)
Shell           -right-> DockerProxy  : /var/run/docker.sock\n(optional layer)
DockerProxy     -right-> SSHAgent     : filtered API calls\nto rootless daemon

@enduml
